node.title: Victoria records 1,221 new local COVID-19 cases and four deaths
node.alt: A photo at road level of a rainy, empty street in Melbourne's CBD.
node.description: There are now 16,671 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 407 people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,221\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and four\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 16,671\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 407\u00a0people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are now 405\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19 in Victoria, of whom 77\u00a0are in intensive care\u00a0and 51\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The new cases were identified from 60,818\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 10,708 vaccine doses administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
How to take a rapid antigen test.
"]
